    <briefdescription>
<para>Structure representing a transition formula using a graph. </para>
    </briefdescription>
    <detaileddescription>
<para>A node of graph consists of node itself and set of children nodes. Nodes are operators and operands of the formula. E.g., a formula q1 &amp; s1 will be transformed to a tree with &amp; as a root node and q1 and s2 being children nodes of the root. </para>
    </detaileddescription>
